  "prompt": "What does Hillary Clinton think of high-skill immigration?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has generally expressed support for high-skill immigration, recognizing its potential benefits for the economy and innovation in the United States. Throughout her political career, she has highlighted the importance of attracting talented individuals from around the world to contribute to various sectors, including technology and research. Clinton has advocated for policies that make it easier for highly skilled professionals to immigrate and work in the U.S., viewing this as integral to maintaining the country's competitive edge globally.\n\nHowever, her exact stance can evolve, and specific details may vary over time and in different contexts. For the most current and detailed understanding of her views, it is best to consult her recent statements, writings, or policy proposals.",
